57:53.929 --> 57:57.099
Frank Sinatra: <i>♪ Buy a hacienda
for a few pesos down... ♪</i>

57:57.141 --> 58:00.311
Irving: <i>Frank Sinatra
sang it so beautifully.</i>

58:02.855 --> 58:06.315
<i>I compose music every day.</i>

58:11.197 --> 58:13.737
<i>A man comes in,</i>

58:13.782 --> 58:16.162
and I happened to be
playing a Latin song.

58:16.202 --> 58:18.832
He looks at me.

58:18.871 --> 58:23.001
He says, "Hey, you play
like a Cubano."

58:23.042 --> 58:25.542
He thought I was Cuban.

58:25.586 --> 58:28.796
<i>"I said," No, no, I'm not Cuban.</i>

58:28.839 --> 58:31.089
I'm a Latin from Manhattan."

58:36.096 --> 58:39.426
And something came to my mind...

58:39.475 --> 58:41.765
Music, notes...

58:43.520 --> 58:45.520
<i>a creative idea.</i>

58:48.484 --> 58:53.534
And I wrote a song called
"A Latin from Manhattan."

58:55.866 --> 59:00.446
I do things today
at my age, at 100,

59:00.496 --> 59:04.366
<i>that I was afraid to do
40, 50 years ago.</i>

59:04.416 --> 59:06.416
It was too difficult for me,

59:06.460 --> 59:08.500
and now it's a piece of cake.

59:11.590 --> 59:14.840
<i>I don't know why, but my
fingers go like lightning</i>

59:14.885 --> 59:16.795
<i>and I play better.</i>

59:16.845 --> 59:18.425
I'm unstoppable.

59:18.472 --> 59:21.352
♪ I'm a Latin from Manhattan ♪

59:21.392 --> 59:24.352
♪ I'm a Latin from Manhattan ♪

59:24.395 --> 59:27.305
♪ I'm a Latin from Manhattan. ♪

59:27.356 --> 59:29.056
Same thing.

59:29.108 --> 59:30.608
<i>A lot of people ask me,</i>

59:30.651 --> 59:33.441
"How come you don't have
any wrinkles?"

59:33.487 --> 59:36.197
100 years old, no wrinkles.

59:36.240 --> 59:38.570
Every morning,

59:38.617 --> 59:42.867
I wash my face
with ice-cold water.

59:46.333 --> 59:50.173
<i>I could work nine days a week
and not be tired.</i>

59:50.212 --> 59:55.222
I go on and on and on
because I love what I do.

59:58.470 --> 01:00:00.010
Most people are interested

01:00:00.055 --> 01:00:02.135
in living a long and
fruitful life that you have.

01:00:02.182 --> 01:00:04.812
Fruit is good, too.
You mentioned fruit.

01:00:04.852 --> 01:00:07.232
Fruit kept me going
for 140 years once

01:00:07.271 --> 01:00:10.481
when I was
on a very strict diet.

01:00:10.524 --> 01:00:13.484
Mainly nectarines.
I love that fruit.

01:00:13.527 --> 01:00:15.437
It's half a peach, half a plum.

01:00:15.487 --> 01:00:17.987
Such a hell of a fruit.
I love it.

01:00:18.032 --> 01:00:19.822
- What has been...
- Even a rotten one.

01:00:19.867 --> 01:00:22.197
A rotten one. That's
how much I love...

01:00:26.874 --> 01:00:31.634
Reiner: <i>Someone who has a real
