01:00:31.670 --> 01:00:35.210
<i>one of the most celebrated
portraitists in the country.</i>

01:00:39.636 --> 01:00:43.056
Olivere: <i>I spend almost all
the time in the studio.</i>

01:00:43.098 --> 01:00:46.558
<i>This is my life here.
It's at the easel.</i>

01:00:51.899 --> 01:00:55.229
<i>I started art school
at the age of 10 in Wilmington.</i>

01:00:57.029 --> 01:00:58.859
<i>I became an illustrator</i>

01:00:58.906 --> 01:01:02.116
<i>for an advertising agency
on Madison Avenue.</i>

01:01:02.159 --> 01:01:04.279
I was a Mad boy.

01:01:06.121 --> 01:01:09.211
<i>And then my wife got me
into portrait painting,</i>

01:01:09.249 --> 01:01:11.419
<i>and that's what
I've been doing ever since.</i>

01:01:13.754 --> 01:01:16.304
<i>Sometimes you get
very excited about an idea.</i>

01:01:18.175 --> 01:01:20.715
I remember waking up
in the middle of the night

01:01:20.761 --> 01:01:22.721
and getting a bolt of lightning

01:01:22.763 --> 01:01:24.763
<i>and getting up out of bed
and running</i>

01:01:24.807 --> 01:01:27.517
to the drawing board
and making sketches.

01:01:30.687 --> 01:01:35.317
In my filing cabinet, I have
many files of just ideas.

01:01:41.281 --> 01:01:43.571
<i>What motivates me is the desire</i>

01:01:43.617 --> 01:01:46.657
<i>to continually create
new things.</i>

01:01:48.288 --> 01:01:50.788
<i>Just don't lose your curiosity.</i>

01:01:50.833 --> 01:01:53.673
<i>That's the big thing...
Being curious.</i>

01:01:53.710 --> 01:01:55.790
Once you lose your curiosity,

01:01:55.838 --> 01:01:59.458
you might as well
lie down and die.

