Tony Bennett asked me
to give the commencement speech

01:02:06.640 --> 01:02:11.180
at the high school for the performing
arts that he founded in Queens

01:02:11.228 --> 01:02:15.268
<i>called the Frank Sinatra School
for the Performing Arts.</i>

01:02:15.315 --> 01:02:17.105
I gave my commencement speech,

01:02:17.151 --> 01:02:21.191
which was
my three principles of life.

01:02:21.238 --> 01:02:23.568
One is bust your ass.

01:02:23.615 --> 01:02:25.735
Whatever you're doing,
bust your ass.

01:02:25.784 --> 01:02:28.334
Work as hard
as you possibly can.

01:02:28.370 --> 01:02:31.500
<i>My second principle
is pay attention.</i>

01:02:31.540 --> 01:02:35.000
Pay attention to what's
around you all the time.

01:02:35.043 --> 01:02:37.673
Appreciate what's around you
all the time.

01:02:37.713 --> 01:02:40.883
And my third principle of life
is fall in love.

01:02:40.924 --> 01:02:45.014
Fall in love, and love
doesn't mean romantic love.

01:02:45.053 --> 01:02:48.013
I believe fall in love
with your parking space.

01:02:48.056 --> 01:02:51.476
And this is something
I kind of got from George Burns.

01:02:51.518 --> 01:02:54.018
<i>"He would say," This cup
of coffee, I think,</i>

01:02:54.062 --> 01:02:56.522
<i>might be the greatest one
I've ever had."</i>

01:02:56.565 --> 01:03:00.065
It's kind of an old-school
virtue, I think.

01:03:00.110 --> 01:03:03.200
I don't know too many
young people that have this.

01:03:03.238 --> 01:03:05.738
I know a lot of older people
that have it.

01:03:13.207 --> 01:03:15.787
I think getting dressed
is a creative experience,

01:03:15.834 --> 01:03:17.384
and I do it my way.

01:03:17.419 --> 01:03:19.099
I'm not really interested
in being current.

01:03:23.175 --> 01:03:26.085
<i>I think if you know who you
are and what your style is,</i>

01:03:26.136 --> 01:03:27.136
you'll always look good.

01:03:28.472 --> 01:03:29.682
Can I just tell you?

